Winchester Supreme Elite PDX1 ammunition was tested by the FBI to see if it can stand up to real world, life threatening situations, this ammunition has impressive expansion and notable velocities at various ranges thanks to Winchester's proprietary bonding process. Factoring in everything I have included in the package with the gun, I feel that asking $750 is more than fair for all of it - especially considering you are lucky to find an AR-15 for less than $800-900 right now with just the gun. title: For Sale:  Colt Model 1902 Alaskan -- U.S Contract .45 Caliber Revolver - C&R OK
postcontent: In 1902, 4,600 Model 1878 revolvers were produced for a U.S. Army contract. These revolvers had a 6 inch barrel, a hard rubber grip, and were chambered for the .45 Colt round. They also had a larger trigger guard and a longer trigger. Many people have incorrectly assumed that this was to allow the revolver to be operated while wearing gloves, but in reality, the larger trigger guard and longer trigger were in response to the Model 1878's reputation for having a very hard trigger pull. The longer trigger was designed to give the user more leverage, thus reducing the perceived force required to pull the trigger. These were called "Alaskan" or "Philippine" revolvers, as they were originally intended for use in Alaska but ended up being shipped to the Philippines. This gun will be a prize for your collection or a fun toy for the range - after some action work of course. Parts should be obtainable for this gun.
